org.diirt.graphene

Interface Point1DDataset


  • public interface Point1DDataset
    A dataset consisting on a set of 1D points.

    It represents a list of ordered values, and their statistical information. The order may not be meaningful, but can be used to identify the points.

    Author:
    carcassi

    • Method Detail

      • getValues

        ListNumber getValues()
        The values of the points.

        If the dataset is empty, it returns an empty list.

        Returns:
        the values; never null

      • getStatistics

        Statistics getStatistics()
        The statistical information of the values.

        If the dataset is empty, or if it contains only NaN values, it returns null.

        Returns:
        statistical information; null if no actual values in the dataset

      • getDisplayRange

        Range getDisplayRange()
        The suggested range to display the values.
        Returns:
        the suggested display range

      • getCount

        int getCount()
        The number of points in the dataset.

        This number matches the size of the list returned by getValues().

        Returns:
        the number of values in this dataset
